The paper deals with the computational complexity of a problem related to formal languages, specifically the Frobenius monoid problem. This suggests that cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a likely sub-category. The paper also involves questions about rewriting systems, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of complexity theory and the PSPACE-completeness result suggest cs.CC as a likely sub-category. The paper also involves questions about mortality, which could fall under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Finally, the paper mentions an inclusion variant of the problem, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory).
